// Embedded `@allocator(bumpalo)` fixture for the e2e CI lane (#547).
//
// The e2e CI lane links every `tests/*.gr` against `runtime/gradient_runtime.c`
// ONLY (no variant runtime crates) — see Pitfall 1 of
// `gradient-runtime-modularization-pattern.md`. This fixture proves the
// bumpalo attribute round-trips through the host parser cleanly while
// NOT calling any heap-allocating builtin that would force a real
// allocator invocation. The bumpalo allocator's `__gradient_alloc` /
// `__gradient_free` symbols are therefore unused in this fixture and
// the linker has nothing to bind to — heap-free pure-arithmetic body
// keeps the link clean against the canonical runtime alone.
//
// The integration tests under `codebase/build-system/tests/allocator_runtime.rs`
// exercise the FULL link path (canonical runtime + variant bumpalo
// runtime crate) and prove the binary actually runs.

@allocator(bumpalo)

fn main() -> !{IO} ():
    print_int(13)
